<subSubSection id="229B3834E7FB29E342E6E401362E65A2" pageId="10" pageNumber="59" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="027FFE721E8A102519738BCA9A3B0D31" pageId="10" pageNumber="59">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="48ABACE1B902A01957C3C50FABEE3405" pageId="10" pageNumber="59">This species is named after the Darien province, locality of the type and paratype collections.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="D32C0A4E0393CCAD1D43FB8FFF5FE6A8" pageId="10" pageNumber="59" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8A269A19D1A155E04E6182D782FA0C4D" pageId="10" pageNumber="59">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B90E6336166D147E3A01B538C74EB761" pageId="10" pageNumber="59">
<taxonomicName id="53554FE80807EBBF46150026DF6DCD5B" authorityName="A. K. Monro" authorityYear="2012" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Solanaceae" genus="Cestrum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Tubiflorae" pageId="10" pageNumber="59" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="darienense">
<emphasis id="117517D9AA811508B7771614BE76199F" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="59">Cestrum darienense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known from two localities in Cerro Pirre and whilst none of the collection labels indicate a forest type, altitude information would suggest that this would be cloud forest. Cerro Pirre covers an area of ca. 50 
<normalizedToken id="F00661A21EE5CA605267A540D7586153" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
25 km. Using collection label data and 
<bibRefCitation id="6314FF780EAA154B07A013B503FFE300" author="Google Earth, 6.0.3.2197" journalOrPublisher="Candollea" pageId="25" pageNumber="74" refId="B7" refString="Google Earth, 6.0.3.2197, 2011. Available from http://www.google.com/earth." title="Available from http: // www. google. com / earth" year="2011">Google Earth</bibRefCitation>
(accesssed June 7, 2011; images from 2003) the Extent of Occurrence for this species is calculated to be ca. 280 km2.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A9AA71DCADA3888787326BD5CA224702" pageId="10" pageNumber="59" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="F79FD916A912D74C1E749D27BBF2A1B2" pageId="10" pageNumber="59">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C7D7F0AF8DD15D657327A3BD03A0C7B9" pageId="10" pageNumber="59">
Of the three collections of 
<taxonomicName id="DB7C9947E91420CB8EF93E25789FA277" authorityName="A. K. Monro" authorityYear="2012" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Solanaceae" genus="Cestrum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Tubiflorae" pageId="10" pageNumber="59" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="darienense">
<emphasis id="AB584A434D4A05EFF75E310EFB042F2C" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="59">Cestrum darienense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
seen, none had been previously determined to species prior to this study. A comparison of the holotype and paratype material with type specimens from the herbaria listed in the Materials and methods section recovered 
<taxonomicName id="5CBF45A26F28AE36853F2AF14FED2778" authorityName="A. K. Monro" authorityYear="2012" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Solanaceae" genus="Cestrum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Tubiflorae" pageId="10" pageNumber="59" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="darienense">
<emphasis id="6C44BADA0C549B057D306174564D979D" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="59">Cestrum darienense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="0B05226411E8DE42CCC5A75987ED0202" authorityName="A. K. Monro" authorityYear="2012" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Solanaceae" genus="Cestrum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Tubiflorae" pageId="10" pageNumber="59" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="gilliae">
<emphasis id="CFB5250C669AC44BB98AB46F02AF9E0A" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="59">Cestrum gilliae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
A.K. Monro and 
<taxonomicName id="C6ACA70DA6E2B27E786DDBA028F8D344" authorityName="A. T. Hunziker" authorityYear="1980" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Solanaceae" genus="Cestrum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Tubiflorae" pageId="10" pageNumber="59" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="morae">
<emphasis id="786C45A82C0C45BCD8F93435E0A4BF00" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="59">Cestrum morae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Hunz. Together with 
<taxonomicName id="90CC55F148867224095A87B60D99773D" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Solanaceae" genus="Cestrum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Tubiflorae" pageId="10" pageNumber="59" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="langeanum">
<emphasis id="7632A18BDB5C5636BCDA73A9556B7ED4" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="59">Cestrum langeanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="EF1AD96587B67CAED2BE241C587EBF68" originalValue="D’Arcy">D'Arcy</normalizedToken>
, 
<taxonomicName id="39FC98D5A7FA94985C5B63D481BCA0C1" authorityName="A. K. Monro" authorityYear="2012" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Solanaceae" genus="Cestrum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Tubiflorae" pageId="10" pageNumber="59" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="darienense">
<emphasis id="07FC15529167337A140C0C5C12A5107C" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="59">Cestrum darienense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="89154F4CC09896C70B9C1A0539B2B991" authorityName="A. K. Monro" authorityYear="2012" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Solanaceae" genus="Cestrum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Tubiflorae" pageId="10" pageNumber="59" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="gilliae">
<emphasis id="698EE42FD9BBEA743357DAFC2D46A1FE" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="59">Cestrum gilliae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="E303E3C29E0A184CDD9CFDAD62273381" authorityName="A. T. Hunziker" authorityYear="1980" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Solanaceae" genus="Cestrum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Tubiflorae" pageId="10" pageNumber="59" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="morae">
<emphasis id="95A77B02F13F10E426A57F4024F6DB6B" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="59">Cestrum morae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
form a coherent morphological and geographical grouping within the genus of species from western Panama and the 
<normalizedToken id="1A08A0608AE34EC319C81A71921C28D0" originalValue="Chocó">Choco</normalizedToken>
in Colombia and Ecuador characterised by broad, nearly three-veined leaves and determinate inflorescences. 
<taxonomicName id="BC91FC3A260CDD771A65E5F8C9EFB7B7" authorityName="A. K. Monro" authorityYear="2012" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Solanaceae" genus="Cestrum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Tubiflorae" pageId="10" pageNumber="59" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="darienense">
<emphasis id="25AE5C9F4C0D6D51B3F4E440BCD25D74" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="59">Cestrum darienense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="5F3B1BC716D49320E005D04A66C1E0FD" authorityName="A. T. Hunziker" authorityYear="1980" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Solanaceae" genus="Cestrum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Tubiflorae" pageId="10" pageNumber="59" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="morae">
<emphasis id="B7E2EC456F5ACA544913D645C6924C96" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="59">Cestrum morae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="CA0DC9B0AB187150CF552F97B5D06E2A" authorityName="A. K. Monro" authorityYear="2012" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Solanaceae" genus="Cestrum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Tubiflorae" pageId="10" pageNumber="59" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="gilliae">
<emphasis id="85130B4E7097723A0D20EB0E410E35D0" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="59">Cestrum gilliae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on the basis of stem, leaf, inflorescence and flower morphology as summarised in 
